During the Winter War, a military conflict between the Soviet Union and Finland in 1939–1940, led to the loss of Karelia and Viipuri for the Fins, the instruments and the mascotte were rescued in a last minute effort and brought by train to Helsinki. This orchestra plays music and songs aimed at refugees from Karelia and their descendants. The band is from Helsinki, whose members are either professional musicians or otherwise advanced musicians.  Its conductors are Tom Bildo and Heino Koistinen.

After The Beatles stopped touring in 1966 he carried on assisting them until their break-up in 1970. He co-wrote You and Me Babe with George Harrison. Evans was killed by police on 5 January 1976, at his home in Los Angeles.

comments: The very first popular Afrikaans singer/songwriter, who remained a well-known musical figure for over three decades. He composed most of his own songs or translated existing songs into Afrikaans. Around 1923 he became the first singer, whose songs were broadcast over the radio, while his first recorded songs appeared in 1929. Blignaut was also the first South African singer who acted in short films for the African silver screen. He recorded using the alias Harold Wise. He was pictured on one of a set of 10 "standard postage" South African commemorative postage stamps celebrating "South African popular music legends" issued in 2015.
